<doc id="292088" wikidata="Q3405692" url="?curid=292088" title="1945 Governor General's Awards">
<text>The 1945 Governor General&#x27;s Awards for Literary Merit were the 10th rendition of the Governor General&#x27;s Awards, Canada&#x27;s annual national awards program which then comprised literary awards alone. The awards recognized Canadian writers for new English-language works published in Canada during 1945 and were presented in 1946. There were no cash prizes.

As every year from 1942 to 1948, there two awards for non-fiction, and four awards in the three established categories, which recognized English-language works only.

== Winners ==

* Fiction: Hugh MacLennan, &quot;Two Solitudes&quot;
* Poetry or drama: Earle Birney, &quot;Now is Time&quot;
* Non-fiction: Evelyn M. Richardson, &quot;We Keep a Light&quot;
* Non-fiction: Ross Munro, &quot;Gauntlet to Overlord&quot;

