<doc id="292104" wikidata="Q3405697" url="?curid=292104" title="1947 Governor General's Awards">
<text>The 1947 Governor General&#x27;s Awards for Literary Merit were the 12th rendition of the Governor General&#x27;s Awards, Canada&#x27;s annual national awards program which then comprised literary awards alone. The awards recognized Canadian writers for new English-language works published in Canada during 1947 and were presented early in 1948. There were no cash prizes.

As every year from 1942 to 1948, there two awards for non-fiction, and four awards in the three established categories, which recognized English-language works only.

==Winners==
* Fiction: Gabrielle Roy, &quot;The Tin Flute&quot;
* Poetry or drama: Dorothy Livesay, &quot;Poems for People&quot;
* Non-fiction: William Sclater, &quot;Haida&quot;
* Non-fiction: R. MacGregor Dawson, &quot;The Government of Canada&quot;

==References==</text><links>
